medicine_summary: Aspirin is a nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to reduce pain, inflammation, and fever. It is also used to prevent blood clots and reduce the risk of heart attacks and strokes
medicine_description: Aspirin is a widely used medication known for its pain-relieving, anti-inflammatory, and antipyretic (fever-reducing) properties. It is also used as a blood-thinning agent to prevent cardiovascular events.
